  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Step 1",
      "body": "Cut 6 - 1×4″ to 22″ (side slates)"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 2",
      "body": "Cut 3 - 1×4″ to 24″ (bottom slates)"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 3",
      "body": "Cut 6 - 1×4″ to 15″ (small side slates)"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 4",
      "body": "Cut 4 - 1×1″ to 12″ (inner supports – we ripped ours from 2×2’s.)",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/7d618afe0ab4e8db.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 5",
      "body": "After you make all your cuts, get started nailing it together! I started by gluing and nailing the long sides to the 1×1’s first.\nNote-Make sure to place the 1×1 flush with the bottom of your 1×4 so that it will not be as noticeable from the top.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/27a04a153a49d29b.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 6",
      "body": "After both longer sides are together, nail on the 1x4's on each end. You may have to trim a little off of each board before nailing in place to make sure that they sit flush on the corners.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/c23189ce05b1eb25.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 7",
      "body": "After we nailed the bottom slates on, we added feet made from round dowels that we had. This step is completely optional. I just like the cuteness that they added!",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/2d32854d6969faa3.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 8",
      "body": "Before staining, I sanded and sanded and sanded some more! It can be a little difficult to get into all the cracks. You might do better to sand before putting it together. It’s completely up to you. Once I finished sanding the crate I stained it with a dark walnut stain by Rust Oleum. I used a q-tip to get the stain into all the little grooves.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/c9428f57e5fa13c8.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 9",
      "body": "Let it dry over night before putting anything in it.\nThe next day I added the word “Pillows” on white vinyl using my Silhouette Cameo. You could easily paint this on your crate if you don’t own a Silhouette or Cricket.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/e6aaaec4bd3acb06.webp"
    }
  ],
